East 36th Street, north side, east of Second Avenue (foreground), showing demolition for the plaza
approach to the Midtown Queens tunnel.
Standing intact in all views is the St. Gabriel's branch of the New York Public Library. This is the last of the building remaining on the "plaza" and it too will be
razed in early 1940.
Adjoining same and partially destroyed in the early views are St. Gabriel's Hall and Parochial School. To the extreme right appear buildings on the east side of First Avenue, between 36th and 37th Streets.
